    "body": "### Problem\n\nHi all, with the `neovim` 0.10.0 syntax changes some old plugins broke in a non-fixable way specifically I would like MultipleSearch plugin to be fixed. \n\nMeovim should fail safely if cterm groups are set to hex values. For example\n```\nhighlight Multiple search ctermfg=#ffffaf ctermbg=#d7ff87 guifg=#ffffaf guibg=#d7ff87 \n```\nToday is broken with error: `Color name or number not recognized`\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5de2f57d-65eb-4a3c-95a4-8002c30df3d7)\n\nI have temporarily fixed the error by modifying the source of MutlipleSearch plugin and removing the cterm colors entirely [here](https://github.com/vim-scripts/MultipleSearch/blob/aada883338fbc80016af68450c2178fbe32d29c7/autoload/MultipleSearch.vim#L116-L118). \n\nI appreciate that MultipleSearch is an ancient plugin, however, we should aim to maintain back-compatibility as much as possible. \n\nThank you. \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nMinimal config\n```\nuse 'vim-scripts/MultipleSearch'\nlet g:MultipleSearchColorSequence = \"#ffffaf\"\nlet g:MultipleSearchMaxColors = 1\n\n:Search anytext\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nneovim to ignore fields that are not used, even if miss-configured. Ideally MultipleSearch would allow setting cterm and gui separately, I think in the past users were expected to handle highlights complexity in their RC i.e. if running in GUI mode set hex codes if running in term mode set known color values. \n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.2 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1727870382\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmac\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niterm2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
